radiographic_examinations.findings: Tracheostomy tube terminates in the mid trachea, 2.6 cm above the carina. Right ventricular pacemaker/defibrillator courses in expected position. Nasogastric tube terminates in the stomach, Dobbhoff tube tip is in the proximal duodenum. No significant pneumothorax. Low lung volumes with increased left lower lobe atelectasis. Moderate cardiomegaly, central venous congestion, and interstitial/airspace edema persist. Aorta is tortuous and calcified.
